ensure the consistency, reproducibility, automation,

00:38:30.679 --> 00:38:34.399
compliance, because there's already a lot of tools around our

00:38:34.399 --> 00:38:39.239
package that allow you to do the analysis and do some compliance

00:38:39.239 --> 00:38:43.239
check. So that's one way we're thinking our package structure

00:38:43.280 --> 00:38:46.679
can potentially be used to organize all those things

00:38:46.679 --> 00:38:53.120
together. And also for project management. So we also recommend

00:38:53.120 --> 00:38:57.560
people to think in a trial way. So set up for success, and work

00:38:57.560 --> 00:39:00.520
as a team, because you always have a multi-functional algorithm

00:39:00.520 --> 00:39:04.159
to work together for the trial. We're also interested to design

00:39:04.159 --> 00:39:07.360
clean code structure, right, to make sure you have proper

00:39:07.360 --> 00:39:10.520
documentation, and relationship between all the functions so

00:39:10.520 --> 00:39:13.439
other people can understand when they translate from project to

00:39:13.439 --> 00:39:16.879
analysis. And also it's necessary to set capability

00:39:16.879 --> 00:39:19.800
boundary, right? In that way, people can cross-boundary to

00:39:19.919 --> 00:39:25.000
help, but also be clear the responsibility of each role. And

00:39:25.000 --> 00:39:27.919
also importantly, we would recommend people to contribute

00:39:27.919 --> 00:39:31.879
to the community. When you feel like a tool that doesn't relate

00:39:31.879 --> 00:39:35.719
to the business logic, that can be a standalone R package, I

00:39:35.719 --> 00:39:39.760
would like to share to the open space. In that way, we can

00:39:39.760 --> 00:39:42.959
continue to grow and to find a consensus to improve the

00:39:42.959 --> 00:39:46.679
workflow across the farm. And when we got to the software

00:39:46.679 --> 00:39:49.760
development life cycle, it should also follow several

00:39:49.760 --> 00:39:52.919
steps, like planning, development edition, operation

00:39:52.919 --> 00:39:56.879
part. So in each of the steps, you need to be properly handled

00:39:56.879 --> 00:40:00.040
for internal development R package, and also need to be

00:40:00.080 --> 00:40:03.959
handled to qualify the external R package. So those

00:40:03.959 --> 00:40:07.280
information can be referred to the R validation hub, white

00:40:07.280 --> 00:40:13.080
paper, how the organization can achieve that. And there are many

00:40:13.080 --> 00:40:16.439
cross-industry collaborations. So the work here cannot be

00:40:16.439 --> 00:40:19.840
achieved without all those outstanding collaborations with

00:40:19.840 --> 00:40:24.120
people from across pharma. So for example, if your interest is

00:40:24.120 --> 00:40:27.879
to understand how to qualify external R package, I would

00:40:27.879 --> 00:40:31.199
suggest to go to R validation hub website and potentially join

00:40:31.199 --> 00:40:34.520
the working group. And there are several presentations being

00:40:34.520 --> 00:40:38.239
handled previously to understand the workflow and tools

00:40:38.239 --> 00:40:42.120
available. And for this talk, we discuss R-based submission

00:40:42.120 --> 00:40:47.239
pilot, and more future work. So more than welcome to check the

00:40:47.239 --> 00:40:52.760
website and join and contribute. And also, the R in pharma

00:40:52.760 --> 00:40:57.520
conference is just wonderful. It helps us a lot to organize

00:40:57.520 --> 00:41:01.879
together to share the ideas and information to collaborate. And

00:41:01.879 --> 00:41:04.520
in addition, the Arkansas Docking Seminar Center is trying

00:41:04.520 --> 00:41:07.399
to share the information including this VITA. So

00:41:07.399 --> 00:41:10.399
continue to share the knowledge across the different organizations

00:41:10.399 --> 00:41:14.719
and it's important to help to shape a better solution towards

00:41:14.719 --> 00:41:19.800
the future. And for the future direction of the current work we

00:41:19.800 --> 00:41:23.080
have, so we still try to enhance the compliance with the

00:41:23.080 --> 00:41:26.639
disability because it began automation, right? We want to

